  "couName": "CPB use",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). A screening sensitivity study was conducted informally during model development to evaluate the influence of inlet turbulence intensity and power-law viscosity exponent on the relative hemolysis index; results indicated low sensitivity across the operating envelope and were documented in the internal technical memo TM-2024-07. That screening exercise informed factor rationales below but was not elevated to a formal structured SensitivityAnalysis node, as the team judged the informal documentation sufficient at MRL 2.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/morrison/req/cpb-hemolysis-mrl2",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/morrison/claim/cpb-hemolysis-worst-case",
